    <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <span class="style8"><strong><span class="style9">Arena Description :<br />
            </span></strong>
            </span>
    <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            Arena -<span class="style8"><br />
            
        <center><a href="images/sanscarburant_arena.jpg">
        <img src="images/sanscarburant_arena.jpg" style="width:auto; height:212px;" /></a>
                </span>
    <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            The Partitioning Wall -<p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <span class="style8"><a href="images/sanscarburant_wall.jpg">
        <img src="images/sanscarburant_wall.jpg" style="width:374px; height:173px;" /></a></center>
                <ol class="style10">
                    <li class="style5">The dimensions of arena are - length: 430cm and width : 90cm.</li>
                    <li class="style5">A wall 90cm wide, with symmetrical ridges of height 45cm feet to 60cm will be dividing
                        the arena into two halves.</li>
                    <li class="style5">
                        <span style="line-height: 115%; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: EN-IN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">
                        The region covering a length </span>of 60cm from either side of the wall is the “no man’s land”. 
                        No tank is allowed to go in this region.</li>
                    <li class="style5">Each side will be divided vertically into 5 equal strips called zones, 30cm each.</li>
                    <li class="style5">The zone in which the tank is kept would be the red zone, the 
                        first adjacent zone either side would be the yellow zone, and the other zone 
                        would be the green zone.</li>
                    <li class="style5">The line of action is 30cm wide along the length of arena.</li>
                    <li class="style5">Two sets of hurdles called Dead zone and the Bushes will be present on either side
                        of line of fight.</li>
                    <li class="style5">Dead Zones will be made of muddy water, and Bushes will be made of leaves/plants/grass
                        etc.</li>
                </ol>
            </span></span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <span class="style8"><strong><span class="style9"><span class="style5">Tank Description :</span><br />
            </span></strong>
                </h3>
                <ol class="style10">
                    <li class="style5">Maximum weight of the tank should be 1800grams.</li>
                    <li class="style5">Maximum area of the tank should be 25cmx20cm, No restrictions is there on the height
                        of the tank.</li>
                    <li class="style5">Muzzle dimension should be42-45 mm.</li>
                    <br />
                    Note:<ol>
                        <li class="style5">The participants may have an adjustable muzzle, that can change its angle so as
                            to hit the opponent accurately. Shooting power can be variable.</li><br />
                        <br />
                        <center>
                            OR<br />
                            <br />
                        </center>
                        You can use different kinds of shooting balls so as to increase or decrease the
                        range of your shoot Three types of balls (44mm diameter) will be provided: Light ball,
                        Medium weighted ball and Heavy ball.
                        <br />
                        <li class="style5">The participant will get some time to adjust his/her tank after each fire.</li>
                    </ol>
                </ol>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <strong><span class="style8">
                <br class="style9" />
            </span></strong>The event will be conducted in two rounds</p>
        <h3 style="color: white; text-align: justify;">
            <u><span class="style6">ROUND 1</span></u>:</h3>
        <ol style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <li class="style5">Participants will place the tank on the strip(which will become the
                red zone), which will be decided on the basis of drawing chits. </li>
            <li class="style5">Hitting on the red zone of your opponent will give 250 points,<br />
                Yellow zone: 200 points<br />
                Green zone: 100 points<br />
                No man’s land: 50 points<br />
                Direct hit on rival’s tank: 400 points <span class="style5"></li>
            <li class="style5">Beware of hitting on-<br />
                Dead zone: -100 points<br />
                Bush: the opponent will get an extra shot<br />
                On same side: - 50 points </li>
            <li class="style5">Hitting the ball outside the arena will fetch no points i.e. 0 points.</li>
            <li class="style5">Each team will be given 10 shots and 5 moves.</li>
            <li class="style5">The participants are free to utilize their moves just after their shot.</li>
    </span>
    <li class="style5">All kinds of missed shots will be counted among the 10 shots given to the team.
    </li>
    <li class="style5">In case of a shot, if the ball fails to leave the muzzle, then it will not be
        considered as a shot.</li>
    <li class="style5">In case team fails to hit the opposition tank and the ball makes 
        a tip(drops) within any zone, in this case the zone of the first tip (drop) will be considered for points.
    </li>
    <li class="style5">Teams are free to use the ball of any material and size which fit the muzzle.</li>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> In case the shot completely damages the opponent’s tank, it directly qualifies to the second round with bonus points.</p>
        </span></ol>
        <h3 style="color: white; text-align: justify;">
            <span class="style6">
            <u>ROUND 2</u></span>:</h3>
        <ol style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify;">
            <li class="style5">Initially the tanks will be kept in the extreme end zones of the arena and that will be considered as the red zone. </li>
            <li class="style5">Hitting within the red zone or tank will earn the team 2 moves forward from the current zone.</li>
            <li class="style5"><span class="style5">Hitting within the adjoining zone i.e. the yellow zone will earn the team 1 move forward from the current zone.</li>
            <li class="style5">Hitting consecutively 2 times on the green zone will earn the team 1 additional move forward (towards the wall).</li>
            <li class="style5">When either of the tanks reaches the “no man’s land”, the position of the opponent’s tank will be locked i.e. no further moves for the rival tank.</li>
            <li class="style5">The tank that reaches first will be given 1 chance to change its position.</li>
       <li class="style5">The tanks will then have to shoot (only 1 shoot will be given to both the tanks) the bulls eye target placed on the either extreme sides of the arena. So the losing tank still has a chance for a comeback.
    </li>
    <li class="style5">Depending on the tank’s accurate hit on the bulls’ eye, points will be awarded.</li>
    <li class="style5">Cumulative score from both the rounds will be considered to chose the winner
    </li>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> In case of any discrepancies, the opinion of the co-ordinators will be final and binding to all.</span></p>
